      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Absolutely, you should definitely go with the RICE method—rest, ice, compression, and elevation. Make sure to keep it elevated above heart level for 20 minutes every hour. You can also use a cold pack wrapped in a towel. If the swelling doesn't start to decrease in 48 hours, consider taking an over-the-counter anti-inflammatory like ibuprofen, but don't exceed the recommended dosage. If the pain and swelling persist, you might want to consider a trip to the doctor. Good luck, and don't forget to keep your ankle elevated!",
